# Validate CI Locally Before Push

**Never commit and push CI changes until the affected steps pass locally.**

See [`scripts/ci/README.md`](../../scripts/ci/README.md) for pipeline layout.

## Minimum checks by change type

| You changed | Run locally before push |
|-------------|-------------------------|
| Quality / typecheck / lint | `bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh` |
| TS build (`build-ts`, `build-ts-workspace.sh`) | `bash scripts/ci/build-ts-workspace.sh` (from clean `dist/`) |
| Native compile / bindings | `npm run build:debug:local` in `packages/bindings/` (or `npm run ci:verify:linux` for full matrix) |
| Integration / test scripts | `bash scripts/ci/run-pr-integration.sh` (needs linux-gnu `.node`) |
| Any CI script or workflow | At least `bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh`; prefer `npm run ci:verify:checks:docker` when Docker is available |
| Release / main workflows | Also confirm reusable workflow callers still match (`build-main.yml`, `release.yml`) |

## Full local mirrors

```bash
bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh          # PR quality job
bash scripts/ci/build-ts-workspace.sh        # PR build-ts job
npm run ci:verify:checks:docker              # quality + integration in ci-build image
npm run ci:verify:linux                      # release Linux cross-builds
npm run ci:verify                            # both
```

## Workflow

1. Make CI change
2. Run the matching local command(s) above — fix failures **before** commit
3. Update [`scripts/ci/README.md`](../../scripts/ci/README.md) if behavior changed
4. Commit → ask user if push confirmation is required → push → watch GitHub Actions

## Do not push when

- Local script exits non-zero
- You only fixed one pipeline without checking callers (see `ci-validation.mdc`)
- TS build was not tested from **clean** `packages/*/dist` (catches sdk↔signaling cycle bugs)
